The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                 NATION BRIEFS
                              
	Bhubaneswar: Repolling has been ordered at eight polling stations, where voting could not be conducted or were disrupted during the first phase of polling.          
	Orissas chief electoral officer Alaka Panda said repoll would be held on Monday at two booths under Bolangir and Aska Lok Sabha constituencies and one booth each under Koraput, Kalahandi, Sundaragarh and Sambalpur parliamentary constituencies. Security and polling arrangements have been made for smooth conduct of second phase polling scheduled on April 23, she said.                  
	Bhubaneswar: Dubbed communal by other parties, including its former coalition partner BJD, the BJP on Sunday alleged that chief minister and BJD boss Naveen Patnaik was indulging in communal politics in Orissa at a news conference. BJD is toeing the Congress line of minority appeasement, BJP state unit president Suresh Pujari. Minority appeasement is in a way communal politics, said the saffron party state chief. He stated that BJD was an offspring of the Congress and alleged that this election the two parties had a tacit understanding to help each other. Any vote for BJD would ultimately go to UPA, he said.                  
	Saharsa: A trader was gunned down by a jawan of State Armed Police (SAP) following a quarrel in Pashupalan colony in Bihars Saharsa district late Saturday night. Superintendent of Police Rajesh Kumar said Tarini Das, 51, who runs an eatery, was shot at by SAP jawan Guneshwar Sharma following an altercation over not serving food on time.                                                                                                                           
